[7] Iowa (Osceola and Cherokee Counties): commercial turkeys and poultry
Date: Fri 1 Apr 2022
Source: KCRG [edited]
https://www.kcrg.com/2022/04/01/two-more-cases-bird-flu-found-iowa/


The Iowa Department of Agriculture has confirmed 2 more cases of highly pathogenic avian influenza (HPAI) in Iowa.

The virus was found in a commercial turkey flock in Cherokee County, Iowa, and a flock of commercial layer chickens in Osceola County.

Cases are beginning to rise, as the number of flocks hit with HPAI in the state has grown significantly over the last month [March 2022].

1 Mar 2022 - Pottawattamie, Backyard Mixed Species
6 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista, Commercial Turkey
10 Mar 2022 - Taylor, Commercial Layer Chickens
17 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista, Commercial Layer Chickens
20 Mar 2022 - Warren, Backyard Mixed Species
23 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista, Commercial Turkey
25 Mar 2022 - Franklin, Commercial Pullet Chickens
28 Mar 2022 - Hamilton, Commercial Turkey
28 Mar 2022 - Guthrie, Commercial Layer Chickens
29 Mar 2022 - Buena Vista, Commercial Turkey
31 Mar 2022 - Osceola, Commercial Layer Chickens
31 Mar 2022 - Cherokee, Commercial Turkey

